            <h2>Saudi Arabian Airlines’ Baggage Policy</h2>


            <h3>Checked Baggage Allowance: </h3>

            <p>
                The amount of free checked baggage on all <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/saudi-arabian-airlines.aspx">Saudi Arabian Airlines</a> flights
                is determined by the weight and dimensions of the luggage, as well as the cabin class. For
                international flights, passengers in first and business class can check two bags weighing up to 32
                kg each, while those in guest (economy) class can check two bags weighing up to 23 kg each.
            </p>

            <p>
                Before passing over the luggage to the check-in counter, all flights that conclude in the United
                States and begin in Riyadh must be sealed with secure wrap. Infants are given 23 kg of free check-in
                baggage, and extra baggage is not permitted. A bag's total length, width, and height should not
                exceed 158 cm.
            </p>

            <h3>Carry on Luggage Allowance: </h3>

            <p>
                The handbag's dimensions cannot exceed 115cm, and the document bag's dimensions cannot exceed 100cm.
                Luggage weighing no more than 9kg is allowed for Business/First Class travelers. Passengers in
                Economy Class are permitted to bring one bag weighing up to 7 kilograms.
            </p>

